---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Diego Cuñado — CV" minimal={true}>
  <main>
    <header>
      <h1>Diego Cuñado</h1>
      <p class="role">Head of Product</p>
      <p class="contact">London, UK · diegocunado@gmail.com · +44 74497 10889</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Profile</h2>
      <p>Head of Product with 8+ years building B2B SaaS and marketplace products, with deep hands-on experience designing, deploying, and iterating AI agents. I've nearly doubled conversion rates at scale, shipped enterprise features, and managed products serving thousands of users, all while staying close to the code.</p>
      <p>Outside of my day role, I build and operate AI agents daily: designing prompt logic, orchestrating multi-step workflows, tuning context and memory systems, and iterating based on real-world performance. I understand the full AI agent lifecycle because I live it, from initial design through deployment, monitoring, and continuous optimisation.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>AI Agent Experience</h2>
      <h3>AI Agent Design & Operations <span class="light">Personal projects, 2025–present</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Designed and operate a production AI agent handling autonomous workflows: email outreach, content publishing, social media management, calendar coordination, and multi-platform communications</li>
        <li>Built prompt logic, context management, and memory systems from scratch, iterating based on real usage patterns across thousands of interactions</li>
        <li>Architected agentic workflows spanning voice, chat, and email channels with tool-use orchestration</li>
        <li>Developed ambient memory system using vector databases and semantic search, enabling the agent to surface relevant context proactively across long-running conversations</li>
        <li>Hands-on with Claude API, OpenAI API, prompt engineering, multimodal LLMs, and AI-assisted development (Cursor, Claude Code)</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Chowdown <span class="light">chowdown.me</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Built AI-powered application with autonomous content generation: the AI agent independently writes, publishes, and promotes blog content across multiple platforms</li>
        <li>Designed agent workflows for food recognition (vision APIs), macro calculation, and personalised recommendations</li>
        <li>Live product with real users across 30+ countries</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

      <h3>Hire Space — Head of Product <span class="light">Jan 2024 – Present</span></h3>
      <p class="company-desc">Two-sided marketplace connecting 5,000+ venues with corporate event organisers.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Nearly doubled site-generated bookings through conversion optimisation and flow redesign after platform migration to Next.js</li>
        <li>Increased managed booking win rate from 15% to 21% by identifying drop-off points and introducing AI-assisted productivity tools for the commercial team</li>
        <li>Rebuilt terms acceptance flow with explicit signing process, reducing booking issues from ~10% to ~1%</li>
        <li>Shipped internal tools used daily by 30+ commercial team members, replacing workflows previously managed through email and spreadsheets</li>
        <li>Closed SEO gap with main competitor from 30+ points to under 8 through technical improvements</li>
        <li>Led coordination across Engineering, Sales, Finance, and Operations to align priorities and ship solutions</li>
        <li>Built functional prototypes to validate product ideas before committing engineering time</li>
        <li>Worked directly with enterprise clients on requirements, integrations, and AI roadmap discussions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Hire Space — Senior Product Manager <span class="light">Feb 2021 – Jan 2024</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Launched Arena, a virtual events platform filling the gap between basic tools (Zoom) and complex enterprise solutions (Hopin)</li>
        <li>Increased automatic booking win rate from ~2% to 5% by analysing funnel data and redesigning key touchpoints</li>
        <li>Released Instant Book flow allowing clients to book and pay immediately rather than waiting days in negotiations</li>
        <li>Built MVP corporate portal for centralised event management and reporting</li>
        <li>Managed third-party integrations and worked directly with enterprise clients on requirements</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>JustPark — Product Manager, B2B <span class="light">Oct 2019 – Feb 2021</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Sole PM on Luna, a data portal for multi-site car park operators. Coordinated 20+ developers across the build</li>
        <li>Adapted platform for public sector, winning tenders including Camden, Dundee, and Northern Ireland</li>
        <li>Launched fleet parking solution opening a new revenue stream serving 700k+ potential drivers</li>
        <li>Released parking insurance product in partnership with third-party provider, leading integration and user flow design</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Odicci — Digital Product Manager <span class="light">Oct 2017 – Oct 2019</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Built product roadmap from scratch, prioritising growth features that drove 60% revenue increase</li>
        <li>Ensured GDPR compliance from day one for the data capture platform</li>
        <li>Doubled the number of campaign modules while improving cross-device compatibility</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Technical Skills</h2>
      <div class="skills-grid">
        <div>
          <strong>AI & Agents</strong>
          <p>Prompt engineering, agent design, context/memory systems, vector databases, LLM APIs (Claude, OpenAI), multimodal applications, agentic workflow orchestration</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Data</strong>
          <p>SQL (daily production queries), dashboards, KPIs, funnel analysis</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Development</strong>
          <p>TypeScript/JavaScript, API integrations, AWS, GCP, Vercel</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Enterprise</strong>
          <p>SSO, permissions, integrations, SLAs, compliance</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Education</h2>
      <p>Bachelor of Economics · Universidad Autónoma de Madrid</p>
      <p>Bachelor of Laws · Universidad Autónoma de Madrid</p>
      <p>Scrum Master Certification · Scrum Alliance</p>
    </section>

    <section class="footer-note">
      <p>Spanish (native), English (fluent) · UK since 2012, London area</p>
      <p class="italic">Economics and Law background combined with hands-on technical product experience: analytical rigour and the ability to dive into complex, ambiguous problems and build elegant solutions.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  @media print {
    main { padding: 0 !important; max-width: 100% !important; }
    header { margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important; }
    section { margin-bottom: 0.4rem !important; }
    h2 { margin-top: 0.5rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.2rem !important; font-size: 0.85rem !important; }
    h3 { font-size: 0.8rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.1rem !important; }
    ul { margin: 0.15rem 0 !important; }
    li { font-size: 0.75rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.05rem !important; line-height: 1.3 !important; }
    p { font-size: 0.75rem !important; line-height: 1.3 !important; }
    .skills-grid { gap: 0.3rem !important; }
    @page { margin: 1.2cm; }
  }

  main {
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    background: #fff;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
    padding-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .role {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #444;
    margin: 0.2rem 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .contact {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #666;
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0 0;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
    padding-bottom: 0.2rem;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.2rem 0;
    color: #1a1a1a;
  }

  h3 .light {
    font-weight: normal;
    color: #666;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .company-desc {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #555;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 0.3rem 0;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 0.2rem 0;
  }

  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .skills-grid strong {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .skills-grid p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #444;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .footer-note {
    border-top: 1px solid #ccc;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .footer-note p {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #555;
  }

  .italic {
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
